{"title": "Sudden Death", "content": "A rule in sports, Game Shows and Video Games where an end-of-match tie is broken by playing a special round. As Sudden Death is intended to bring a swift conclusion to the contest, the victory conditions for this final round are usually highly abbreviated - often, the first score wins the match.\n\nIn video games in particular, a common way to achieve this is to put all participants into critical health so that everyone kills and gets killed by each other at the poke of a finger.\n\nFor an actual sudden death of a character, see Dropped a Bridge on Him. For Jean-Claude Van Damme film, see Sudden Death.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuddenDeath", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JeanClaudeVanDamme", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SuddenDeath", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/GundamBuildFightersTry", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DodgeballATrueUnderdogStory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SuddenDeath", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JeanClaudeVanDamme", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/GetThePicture", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThatMitchellAndWebbLook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/FamilyFeud", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CardSharks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoubleDare1986", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/LegendsOfTheHiddenTemple", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Whew", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Jeopardy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Blackout", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Pyramid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Duel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/WheelOfFortune", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Lingo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Taskmaster", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheyThinkItsAllOver", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheWeakestLink", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TeamFortress2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperSmashBros", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Worms", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WiiSportsResort", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GuitarHero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Halo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.p